The paper discusses moving-target defense (MTD) against false data injection (FDI) attacks in power grids, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also uses optimal power flow (OPF) formulation, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses the tradeoffs between detection capability and operational cost, which is a topic related to power systems (cs.PF).
